revision.text:
'''Apostolic Nunciature to Flanders''' was an ecclesiastical office of the [[Catholic Church]] to [[Flanders]], [[Belgium]].<ref name=CathHierNuncioFlanders>{{Cite web|last=Cheney |first=David M.|authorlink=|title=Nunciature to Flanders|publisher=''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''|date=|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dx963.html |accessdate=March 25, 2018}} [[Wikipedia:SPS|{{sup|[''self-published'']}}]]</ref> It was a diplomatic post of the [[Holy See]], whose representative is called the [[Apostolic Nuncio]] with the rank of an [[ambassador]]. The office ceased to exist in 1795 after the annexation of Flanders by [[France]].<ref name=CathHierNuncioFlanders />

