'''Greater Europe''' refers to the idea of an extended or developed [[Europe]]. This generally implies a Europe which transcends traditional boundaries, including [[List of countries spanning more than one continent#Asia and Europe|trans-Eurasian countries]],<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=rHYZk-t7dI0C&pg=PA158&dq=%22Greater+Europe%22+eurasia |title=Russia and the West: the 21st century security environment |page=158 |publisher=M.E. Sharpe |year=1999 |isbn=978-0-7656-0432-3}}</ref> or those in close proximity with a strong European heritage.<ref>[https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9F07E0DB123DF932A15752C0A9669C8B63 Coca-Cola Forms 2 New Overseas Units]; The New York Times; 21 January 2000; retrieved 7 August 2008</ref>

It may specifically deal with [[Future enlargement of the European Union|future scenarios]] of [[enlargement of the European Union|enlargement]] or [[European integration|development]] of the [[European Union]], to the point of a [[Federal Europe]] or the [[Eurosphere]],<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/monitoring/36621.stm Russian media reports on Yeltsin's pledge to cut troops]; BBC News; 3 December 1997; retrieved 7 August 2008</ref><ref>[http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0,1433,1578602,00.html EU and Russia Agree to Strengthen Ties]; DW-world; 10 May 2005; retrieved 7 August 2008</ref><ref>[http://www.euractiv.com/section/central-europe/news/commission-creates-wider-europe-task-force/ Commission creates 'Wider Europe' task force]; EurActiv; 10 July 2003; retrieved 7 August 2008</ref> or a "re-unified" [[Europe]] after [[revolutions of 1989|the fall of the Iron Curtain]].<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=MzlYIgAACAAJ&dq=%22Greater+Europe%22 |title=Towards greater Europe?: a Continent without an iron curtain |publisher=Blackwell Publishers |year=1992 |isbn=978-0-631-18551-2}}</ref>

[[File:EU neighbourhood initiatives.PNG|thumb|center|600px|[[European Union|EU]] regional initiatives; [[Future enlargement of the European Union#States and entities on the current agenda|current enlargement agenda]] ([[Stabilisation and Association Process|SAP]] and candidate countries), [[European Neighbourhood Policy|ENP]]; [[Eastern Partnership]], [[Euro-Mediterranean Partnership]] and [[EU-Russia Common Spaces]]]]

