'''Keilir Golf Club''' is a [[Golf course|golf club and course]] located in [[Hafnarfjördur]], [[Iceland]], on the Hvalreyi peninsula.
Keilir Golf Club was established in 1967. It was originally developed as a nine-hole course by Magnus Gudmundsson.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Daley|first1=Paul|title=Golf Architecture: A Worldwide Perspective, Volume 3|date=2008|publisher=Pelican Publishing Company|isbn=9781589806160|page=94}}</ref>
In 1971, the Swedish golf designer Nils Skjöld expanded the golf course to 12 holes.<ref>{{cite web|title=Keilir Golf Course - Golficeland|url=http://golficeland.org/introduction/keilir-golf-course/}}</ref> The course was expanded to 18-holes by Icelandic golf course designer Hannes Thorsteinsson.
==Tournaments== The [[Amstel Light]] Iceland Open is held jointly at [[Reykjavik Golf Club]] as well as at Keilir Golf Club during the summer solstice at the end of June each year since 2002.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Young|first1=Don|title=Reykjavik Iceland and Its Surroundings|date=2009|publisher=Hunter Publishing Inc.}}</ref> The tee times start at midnight. ==References== {{reflist}}
