{{Infobox civilian attack | title = May 2016 Dürümlü bombing | partof = [[Turkey-PKK conflict]] | image = Latrans-Turkey location Diyarbakır.svg | alt = Diyarbakır | caption = Diyabakir Province highlighted within Turkey | location = [[Diyabakir]], [[Turkey]] | target = Civilians | date = 12 May 2016 | time = 22:30 | timezone = GMT+2 | type = [[Truck bomb]] | fatalities = 16 ({{small|civilians}}) | injuries = 23 ({{small|civilians}}) | perpetrator = [[PKK]] }} {{Campaignbox PKK–Turkey conflict}}
The May 12, 2016 Dürümlü bombing was a [[truck bomb]] attack that took place in Dürümlü hamlet in [[Diyarbakır]]'s Sur district, Turkey on Thursday 12th May 2016 at approximately 22:30 local time. As a result of the attack 16 villagers were killed and 23 villagers were wounded.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/diyarbakirdaki-patlamada-olenlerin-kimlikleri-belli-oldu-40104862|title=Diyarbakır'daki patlamada ölenlerin kimlikleri belli oldu|publisher=|accessdate=27 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sozcu.com.tr/2016/gundem/diyarbakirda-kaybolan-13-koylu-patlamada-parcalanarak-olmus-1232780/|title=Diyarbakır’daki patlamayla ilgili önemli gelişme!|publisher=|accessdate=27 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://aljazeera.com.tr/al-jazeera-ozel/isteseler-patlatmayabilirlerdi|title=‘İsteseler patlatmayabilirlerdi’|publisher=|accessdate=27 July 2016}}</ref> The [[PKK]]'s militant wing, the People's Armed Forces (HPG), later claimed responsibility for the attack in the name of PKK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://anfenglish.com/kurdistan/hpg-statement-on-the-blast-in-amed-s-durumlu-area|title=ANF - Ajansa Nûçeyan a Firatê|publisher=|accessdate=27 July 2016}}</ref>
==See also== *[[February 2016 Diyarbakır bombing]] *[[March 2016 Diyarbakır bombing]] *[[May 2016 Diyarbakır bombing]]
