{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Vilkaviškis |latin = Dioecesis Vilkaviskensis |local = Vyskupija Vilkaviškio |image = Vilkaviškis Švč Mergelės Marijos Apsilankymo katedra (Large).jpg |image_size = 250px |caption = Vilkaviškis Cathedral |country = [[Lithuania]] |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Kaunas|Kaunas]] |province = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Kaunas|Kaunas]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = ''Švč. M. Marijos Apsilankymo katedra'' |cocathedral = |area_km2 = |population = 339,241 |population_as_of = 2014 |catholics = 331,154 |catholics_percent= 97.6 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Rimantas Norvila]] |metro_archbishop = [[Sigitas Tamkevičius]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= |emeritus_bishops = Juozas Žemaitis, M.I.C. |map = Lituania - Diocesi di Vilkaviškis.png |map_caption = Location of Diocese of Vilkaviškis in Lithuania |website = [http://vilkaviskis.lcn.lt/ Website of the Diocese] }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Vilkaviškis''' ({{lang-la| Vilkavisken(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Vilkaviškis]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Kaunas|Kaunas]] in [[Lithuania]]. It was established on April 4, 1926 from the [[Diocese of Łomża]], [[Poland]].
== Special churches == *Minor Basilicas: **''Šv. arkangelo Mykolo bazilika'' (Basilica of [[Michael (archangel)|St. Michael the Archangel]]), [[Marijampolė]].
== Leadership == * [[Bishop]]s of Vilkaviškis (Roman rite) ** Bishop Rimantas Norvila (since 2002.01.05) ** Bishop [[Juozas Žemaitis]], [[Congregation of Marian Fathers|M.I.C.]] (1991.12.24 – 2002.01.05) ** Bishop Juozas Žemaitis, M.I.C. (Apostolic Administrator 1988.04.27 – 1991.12.24) ** Archbishop [[Liudas Povilonis]], M.I.C. (Apostolic Administrator 1979.05.28 – 1988.04.27) ** Bishop [[Antanas Karosas]] (1926.04.05 – 1947.07.07)
